reviewText: ALTHOUGH COURSE WAS VERY INFORMATIVE BUT TOO SHORT AND ALL THESE TOPICS I ALREADY STUDIED IN MBA FINANCE

There is definitely some valuable information in the video lectures. However - despite the lecturers assurance that 'this is not about math' - the majority of the course is taken up by boards after boards of complicated math formulas. A lot of it went completely over my head and made me ultimately drop out. I am aware that I am not a math wizard but not sure if this would truly qualify as a 'beginners' class.
Productive time spent by learning the course. A helpful course like the topic explains itself.

I have nothing but good things to say about my experience with Coursera. I have loved the learning I have been able to do and look forward to taking many more classes with them ... I don't understand the reviews with low ratings. I have never had any problems with them.
